<br>
If toons were available to buy straight from the source, it would ruin the market for eBay sales of powerlevelled toons - assuming VI doesn't charge too much that is.<br>
<br>
It'd also open up the opportunity for guilds to buy accounts as needed but without the hassle of powerleveling a new toon up to 60.<br>
<br>
Kinda like how the repeal of the Prohibition helped ruin many small time crime syndicates - gangs formed just to smuggle liqour.  Once the booze was legit again, noone needed rumrunners.<br>
<br>
If they did it...I'd buy a 60 druid and go kite stuff in ME. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uralkorravenblood.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ralkor Ravenblood</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 48<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/20/02 5:13:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2760.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Let's hope that this is not a trend</span><hr size=1> That would kill any game, where part of the fun is working for something hard to finally see rewards. I think Sony is not THAT stupid.<br>
<br>
